  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once melted, add half <span class=\"text-danger\">[all]</span> the drained <strong>sweetcorn</strong> and a big pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for 2 min or until the sweetcorn has browned slightly&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/524.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/524.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/524.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/524.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/524.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong>&nbsp;basmati rice</strong> and stir to coat the grains</p>\r\n<p>Add&nbsp;300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span>&nbsp;<strong>water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until the water has absorbed and the rice is tender &ndash; this is your <strong>corn</strong> <strong>rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/524.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/524.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/524.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/524.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/524.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the<strong> smoked&nbsp;</strong><strong>paprika</strong> and<strong> ground</strong>&nbsp;<strong>allspice</strong> in a mixing bowl with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>pepper</strong> and 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Place your hand flat onto the <strong>chicken breast fillet<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Slice in half as if you were cutting a burger bun, so you are left with 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> thinner pieces</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> sliced</strong>&nbsp;<strong>chicken</strong> to the spice mix and mix everything up until the chicken is fully coated&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Lato; font-size: 15px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/524.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/524.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/524.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/524.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/524.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate pan with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>spiced</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> and cook for 3-4 min on both&nbsp;sides or until cooked through, then transfer to a clean chopping board</p>\r\n<p>Note: the chicken will appear very dark and burnt &ndash; don't panic, this is how it's meant to be!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/524.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/524.-step-4-x400.jpg",
